Mechanical Waves

Mechanical waves require a medium to propagate. The wave energy is transferred
through the vibration of particles in the medium.

Types
    Transverse waves: Particles move perpendicular to wave direction
    Longitudinal waves: Particles move parallel to wave direction
    Surface waves: Combination of transverse and longitudinal

Properties
    Speed depends on medium properties
    Cannot travel through vacuum
    Energy transfer without matter transport

Examples
    Sound waves, water waves, seismic waves

